# Powershell Basics

## Lab Overview
Brief explanation of what this lab covers.

## Objectives
- Understand how Powershell differs from Command-Line
- Identify fundamental 'cmdlets'
- Learn how Powershell manipulates objects

## Key Concepts

| cmdlets | built-in Powershell commands formated as verb-noun, that return .NET objects |
| Get-Content | cmdlet that tells Windows to read the content of an items, pulls text into Powershell for inspection |
| Set-Location | changes the current workingn location similar to 'cd' in CLI |
| CommandInfo | object type that stores 'metadata' about a command, such as the commands name and type |
| -CommandType | paramenter used with Get-Command to filters commands based on what kind of command they are |
| Get-Help | Provides information about a given command |
| Get-Alias| Used in conjunction with an alias to find 'to which commmand it maps |
| Get-Childitem | lists the items inside a location, similar to 'dir' in CLI |
| Find-Module | searches a registered Powershell repository for 'modules matching a criteria' |
| -Name | common paramenter used to tell a cmdlet which item,command,module,service,alias, property is being searched |
| Function | script-based command written in Powershell syntax |

